than solving a case.

02:17.096 --> 02:19.589
Has anyone seen my Shuffle?
I can't find it anywhere.

02:19.714 --> 02:23.295
A treasured item gone missing.
Are you thinking what I'm thinking?

02:23.420 --> 02:25.248
This sounds like a case for...

02:25.587 --> 02:27.243
Wheels and the Legman!

02:47.142 --> 02:50.935
You know, Wheels and the Legman,
the detective duo we created.

02:51.059 --> 02:53.056
I'm Wheels, and Roger's the Legman.

02:53.238 --> 02:56.667
We've been looking for a case,
but now it appears that case...

02:56.952 --> 02:58.003
found us.

03:01.901 --> 03:05.017
Stop that! Look, if you see my Shuffle,
let me know.

03:05.142 --> 03:07.888
There is, madam,
the small matter of our fee.

03:08.013 --> 03:10.047
$20 a day, plus expenses.

03:10.368 --> 03:12.371
Or that half a turkey sandwich
you left in the fridge.

03:12.496 --> 03:14.229
- That's Dad's.
- We have a deal then.

03:34.677 --> 03:36.245
Why so sad, Mrs. Smith?

03:36.370 --> 03:38.967
It's me, Scott, from Langley Flag
and Boot Cleaning.

03:39.703 --> 03:41.980
Say hi to your husband.
He's my best customer.

03:44.275 --> 03:45.373
Stan's boss!

03:45.809 --> 03:48.086
Francine, I have bad news.

03:50.954 --> 03:54.805
My car broke down two blocks from here
and it's just off warranty.

03:54.930 --> 03:56.213
That's the bad news?

03:56.490 --> 03:58.420
Well, actually, there's more.

03:58.545 --> 03:59.878
Father Carrington?

04:03.129 --> 04:06.542
Mrs. Smith, there's no easy way to say
this, so I'm just going to be direct.

04:06.711 --> 04:07.500
Dear God!

04:07.669 --> 04:10.260
I was caught having sex with a man
and I'm being excommunicated.

04:10.385 --> 04:11.373
What about Stan?

04:12.021 --> 04:15.666
Nope. I don't believe Stan has had sex
with Father Carrington.

04:16.051 --> 04:20.079
Also, we lost communications
with Stan 12 hours ago.

04:21.827 --> 04:24.070
I'm trained for this.
Step aside, please.

04:25.713 --> 04:27.175
There, there.

04:32.069 --> 04:33.532
We're gonna die!

04:33.878 --> 04:35.623
I just know it!
I just really do!

04:35.747 --> 04:38.222
Stay cool, Stan.
We've been trained for this.

04:38.347 --> 04:40.522
I know! But I forget!

04:42.685 --> 04:44.360
There's gotta be a way out of here.

04:44.595 --> 04:45.893
You're relieved.

04:47.836 --> 04:49.484
I think our luck just changed.

05:25.069 --> 05:26.068
Halt!

05:26.519 --> 05:27.618
Don't shoot.

05:48.694 --> 05:49.693
Just go.

05:53.835 --> 05:56.757
All right, Wheels. This is the last
place Hayley saw her Shuffle.

05:56.882 --> 05:59.507
Search her dresser for clues.
I'll take the closet.

06:00.244 --> 06:02.877
- Careful!
- Sorry. I'm a little rusty using the chair.

06:12.701 --> 06:14.825
- Just use your legs!
- We can't break character!

06:14.950 --> 06:17.686
- For crying out loud!
- No, no!

06:18.067 --> 06:20.074
I did it.
Look!

06:22.203 --> 06:24.626
A butt-print on Hayley's bedspread,

06:24.750 --> 06:26.604
way too big to be Hayley's.

06:26.729 --> 06:29.596
There are only two people
who could leave a print that big.

06:31.576 --> 06:33.944
Well, it's not Travolta.
So it's gotta be Barry.

06:37.633 --> 06:40.572
Mama, Stan went on a mission

06:40.696 --> 06:43.387
and he's been missing for five days...

06:44.888 --> 06:47.168
What's that in the background?

06:47.293 --> 06:48.850
You're at a movie?

06:49.398 --> 06:52.075
Well, go in the lobby!
You're being rude!

07:01.384 --> 07:03.307
I thought I'd never see you again!

07:03.432 --> 07:04.739
There, there, Francine.

07:04.864 --> 07:06.475
I promised I'd be home in time

07:06.599 --> 07:08.993
to take you out for
a romantic Valentine's dinner.

07:10.326 --> 07:12.708
If I smell at all like sex,
it's because of Jim.

07:13.356 --> 07:17.360
I was on his heels as he porked
our way through 200 miles of jungle.

07:17.765 --> 07:19.385
His hips never stopped moving.

07:19.510 --> 07:20.755
It was magnificent.

07:21.799 --> 07:24.596
- You're... crushing me.
- It's almost over.

07:28.356 --> 07:31.034
Sorry I didn't have time to get you
a Valentine's Day present.

07:31.158 --> 07:34.214
Just having you home safe
is the only present I need.

07:35.398 --> 07:37.017
You know I'll always come back.

07:37.142 --> 07:38.141
I know,

07:38.586 --> 07:41.048
but sometimes
I think about if you didn't.

07:41.284 --> 07:42.376
And you know what?

07:42.565 --> 07:46.156
I think that would be it
for the romantic part of my life.

07:46.429 --> 07:48.114
And that would be fine,

07:48.239 --> 07:51.118
because I would have known
my soul mate,

07:51.243 --> 07:53.015
my one true love.

07:53.550 --> 07:55.947
That's more than most people ever get.

07:56.180 --> 07:57.817
And the memory of our love

07:57.941 --> 08:01.914
would be enough to sustain me
for the rest of my days alone.

08:02.504 --> 08:03.828
How about you?

08:04.167 --> 08:05.751
What would you do if I died?

08:05.875 --> 08:08.072
I'd marry Meg Penner,
my backup wife.

08:15.218 --> 08:16.217
Meg Penner?

08:16.714 --> 08:18.063
Wait, Dr. Penner?

08:18.209 --> 08:19.237
Our dentist?!

08:19.406 --> 08:22.197
Exactly, that's who I would marry next.
She's my backup.

08:22.322 --> 08:24.688
Like that extra pair of underwear
I keep in the car...

08:24.813 --> 08:26.150
just in case.

08:26.318 --> 08:29.525
You already know who you want
to marry after I'm dead?

08:29.692 --> 08:30.671
It's Nothing formal.

08:30.796 --> 08:33.490
Meg and I were talking
during one of my routine cleanings.

08:33.615 --> 08:35.913
The subject came up, and we decided
that if our spouses die,

08:36.038 --> 08:37.563
we'll marry each other.

08:37.933 --> 08:40.828
Wait, Dr. Penner knows about this?

08:40.953 --> 08:42.884
Francine, listen to yourself.

08:43.009 --> 08:45.360
How crazy would it be to plan
a backup marriage

08:45.485 --> 08:47.340
without alerting the backup bride?

08:47.621 --> 08:49.367
That would just be weird.

08:52.018 --> 08:54.600
- Are you in love with Meg Penner?
- What?

08:54.725 --> 08:56.357
No, no, I'm not in love with her.

08:56.481 --> 08:58.369
- Are you sleeping with her?!
- Of course not!

08:58.494 --> 09:00.894
Then why are you making
all these plans with her?

09:01.019 --> 09:03.920
Oh, baby, baby, you must have misheard
me or misunderstood me.

09:04.045 --> 09:05.503
It was probably my fault.

09:06.730 --> 09:09.541
None of this happens
until you are dead.

09:14.986 --> 09:18.980
Stan, I want you to break off this
crazy arrangement with Dr. Penner.

09:19.297 --> 09:23.088
I'm not dead, and I don't like you
arranging my replacement as if I were!

09:23.212 --> 09:25.071
No. You're making
a big deal out of nothing.

09:25.196 --> 09:26.544
It's not nothing.

09:26.692 --> 09:28.389
Not to a woman at least.

09:28.623 --> 09:31.811
You think Dr. Penner's approaching this
as casually as you are?

09:31.936 --> 09:33.669
Probably.
She's pretty casual.

09:33.794 --> 09:35.706
She wears Crocs around the office.

09:36.411 --> 09:39.176
Look, Francine, they say men
who are happily married

09:39.301 --> 09:41.209
usually get remarried right away.

09:41.334 --> 09:44.130
So, this is actually
a huge compliment to you.

09:44.631 --> 09:46.569
There's your Valentine's Day
present.

09:46.694 --> 09:48.841
Your present is that observation.

09:53.984 --> 09:56.846
We know you were in the victim's room
on the day in question, Barry.

09:56.971 --> 09:59.227
This is the room
where I sleep in my house!

09:59.390 --> 10:00.656
Don't get smart with me!

10:00.926 --> 10:02.896
You wanna do this the hard way,
that's fine.

10:03.021 --> 10:04.363
I invented the hard way!

10:04.623 --> 10:06.959
- What do you think you're doing?
- I'm playing bad cop.

10:07.084 --> 10:09.814
- You know, good cop/bad cop?
- Yeah, but I'm the bad cop.

10:09.939 --> 10:11.619
Roger, I'm the one in a wheelchair.

10:11.744 --> 10:13.838
I'm bitter about my fate
and constantly in pain

10:13.963 --> 10:16.418
