16:01.529 --> 16:04.183
Jim, I'm sorry,
but she's a happily married...

16:07.292 --> 16:08.609
Not anymore!

16:09.919 --> 16:10.866
What the fuck!

16:14.945 --> 16:17.218
You lost your damn mind, Jim?

16:17.343 --> 16:18.541
That was Stan!

16:18.836 --> 16:20.384
You just killed Stan!

16:23.557 --> 16:25.193
All right.
What's done is done.

16:25.318 --> 16:26.626
Can't change it now.

16:26.751 --> 16:28.742
Reggie's just got to keep moving.

16:35.163 --> 16:38.768
And so, on behalf of the Guinness Book
of World Records,

16:38.893 --> 16:41.165
I, Lady Carolyn Gilbert-Lawson,

16:41.290 --> 16:45.296
congratulate Achmed Asadi
for making the world's biggest falafel.

16:52.436 --> 16:53.706
You're a fraud, Asadi!

16:54.044 --> 16:56.141
I just wanted to impress Zamira!

16:56.299 --> 16:57.871
She is so beautiful!

17:05.876 --> 17:08.750
Hey, lady, is that your hot air balloon?
I need a ride back to the States.

17:08.875 --> 17:12.656
I'm sorry, but that balloon
is for official Guinness business only.

17:12.990 --> 17:14.675
What if I told you
we'd set the record

17:14.799 --> 17:17.196
for "Most Spontaneous Cross Atlantic
Hot Air Balloon Trip"?

17:17.507 --> 17:19.273
I'm sorry, sir, I can't...

17:19.398 --> 17:21.263
What if I told you
I'm about to set the record

17:21.388 --> 17:23.684
for shooting a woman in the face
the most times in a row?

17:23.809 --> 17:26.419
Alejandro, fire up the balloon!

17:32.621 --> 17:35.671
Hayley, we worked all day,
and we finally figured everything out.

17:35.796 --> 17:37.617
- Really?
- Yeah, I'm good cop,

17:37.742 --> 17:38.911
pos(192,230)and Roger's bad cop.

17:39.036 --> 17:40.351
pos(192,230)I make the wisecracks,

17:40.476 --> 17:43.211
pos(192,230)but Roger can be sarcastic,
as long as it's not too schticky.

17:43.336 --> 17:46.075
pos(192,230)I get to have the troubled past,
but Steve always gets the girl.

17:46.200 --> 17:48.911
Unless she's a bad guy,
in which case, Roger gets her,

17:49.036 --> 17:51.954
so she can betray him, leading to
a gunfight on the roof of an opera house.

17:52.079 --> 17:53.516
- Or a theater.
- Or a theater.

17:53.742 --> 17:56.301
What the hell are you talking about?
Where's my Shuffle?

17:56.426 --> 17:58.746
- Your what now?
- That was the whole point of this.

17:58.871 --> 18:01.763
You were supposed to find
my iPod Shuffle, rember?

18:02.028 --> 18:03.650
Is that what a Shuffle is?

18:03.775 --> 18:06.392
- I did not realize. Yeah, I took that.
- What?

18:06.517 --> 18:10.123
I was in Hayley's her room, using her toothbrush
to scrub the bird poo out of my red wig.

18:10.248 --> 18:12.544
What? Oh, God, I'm going to be sick.

18:12.933 --> 18:14.930
Can I finish my story, please?

18:15.055 --> 18:16.957
Anyway, I took your iPod
from the dresser

18:17.082 --> 18:18.747
for a variety of complex reasons,

18:18.872 --> 18:20.839
the most important of which
was that it was shiny.

18:21.444 --> 18:23.812
I erased all your music
and filled it with ABBA.

18:23.937 --> 18:25.895
Don't really care for them,
but I did it anyway.

18:26.020 --> 18:29.011
So that explains the red hair
we found in Klaus's bowl.

18:29.135 --> 18:31.917
I guess it wasn't just
a red hair-ing!

18:32.041 --> 18:33.334
Nice pun work, Wheels.

18:33.502 --> 18:34.619
Thanks, Legman.

18:34.744 --> 18:36.675
The puns are there in the marble.

18:36.800 --> 18:39.854
- I just have to chisel them out.
- Free them from the marble.

18:41.943 --> 18:42.997
You need something?

18:46.842 --> 18:49.464
Thanks.
Why do you travel like this, Alejandro?

18:49.589 --> 18:50.827
I'll tell you why, Stan.

18:52.335 --> 18:55.601
Will you put me in the record book
as the happiest man alive

18:55.726 --> 18:59.017
by becoming Mrs. Lady Carolyn
Gilbert Lawson-Rojas?

18:59.359 --> 19:00.418
Yes, Alejandro!

19:00.543 --> 19:02.041
A million times yes!

19:10.615 --> 19:11.429
You!

19:27.282 --> 19:28.896
Francine, help!

19:29.825 --> 19:32.478
I'm dealing with
a little problem of my own.

19:34.997 --> 19:37.182
- What are you doing?
- We're going to be together.

19:37.307 --> 19:38.726
Like we planned.

19:40.107 --> 19:41.808
No, we broke up, remember?

19:42.230 --> 19:43.441
I know. No, I know.

19:43.565 --> 19:45.843
Look, I really tried
to play it cool, but...

19:45.968 --> 19:48.115
But the truth is, you were right.

19:48.461 --> 19:49.459
I love you.

19:49.647 --> 19:52.262
And my heart has a cavity
that only you can fill!

19:53.072 --> 19:54.319
That is clever...

19:54.444 --> 19:56.159
and super-crazy.

19:58.868 --> 20:00.915
Stan, this is all my fault.

20:03.104 --> 20:06.669
I was jealous,
so I tried to make you jealous.

20:08.339 --> 20:10.532
No, it's my fault.

20:10.689 --> 20:13.081
There's a lot of things
you should make backup plans for,

20:13.206 --> 20:15.196
but love isn't one of them.

20:16.424 --> 20:18.303
Stan, that's beautiful.

20:27.132 --> 20:27.957
My tooth!

20:28.233 --> 20:29.706
I can put a crown on for you.

20:29.874 --> 20:31.583
I'm not going to you anymore.

20:31.708 --> 20:33.621
Good luck getting
your x-rays back, bitch!

20:38.150 --> 20:40.494
Nobody shoots my backup husband.

20:41.312 --> 20:43.909
Meg, you saved my life!
I love you!

20:54.428 --> 20:55.553
Just, just...

20:56.943 --> 20:59.312
- Did we just find another case?
- Are you kidding me?

20:59.437 --> 21:00.556
This is gruesome.

21:00.681 --> 21:02.616
This is like a cable crime.
We're network.

21:02.741 --> 21:05.045
- Yeah, no one dies on our show.
- Right.

21:05.169 --> 21:07.727
Let's face it:
On our darkest day, we're Scooby-Doo.

21:07.852 --> 21:09.153
Maybe Quincy.

